 - Motorcycle USA|work=Motorcycle USA|access-date=2017-09-14|language=en-US}}</ref>\n| fuel_capacity = {{convert|14.0|L|abbr=on}}\n| oil_capacity = {{convert|2.1-2.4|L|USqt|abbr=on}}\n| related = [[Yamaha MT-03#2016\u2013present|Yamaha MT-03]]<br/>[[Yamaha YZF-R25]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Yamaha YZF-R3''', commonly known as the \"R3\", is a [[Sport bike|sport]] [[motorcycle]] that has been manufactured by [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]] since 2015. A first for Yamaha twins, the other being [[Yamaha YZF-R25|R25]], the R3 uses an offset cylinder design.<ref name=firstlooks>{{cite web |url=http://www.cycleonline.com.au/2015/05/22/review-2015-yamaha-yzf-r3///|last= Shields |first=Matthew  |title=Review: 2015 Yamaha YZF-R3| publisher=CycleOnline.com.au |accessdate=September 5, 2017|date=May 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe YZF-R3 was updated for 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motorcyclenews.com/news/new-bikes/yamaha-yzf-r3-motogp-aggression/|title=New Yamaha YZF-R3 brings MotoGP aggression to the A2 class|date=2018-10-10|website=Motorcycle News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\n== Design ==\nThe Yamaha R3 is an entry level sport motorcycle,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bestbeginnermotorcycles.com/yamaha-r3-review/|title=Yamaha R3 Review- Pros, Cons, Specs & Ratings|date=2017-01-31|work=BestBeginnerMotorcycles|access-date=2017-09-14|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" />designed to compete with rivals in 250-400&nbsp;cc sector, such as the [[Kawasaki Ninja 300]], [[Honda CBR250R/CBR300R|Honda CBR300R]], and [[KTM 390 series]]. It is designed as a well-balanced sport motorcycle, with some design similarity to [[Yamaha YZF-R25|R25]], such as engine (which is bored out).<ref name=\":4\" /> With a low seat height, the windscreen sufficiently deflects the wind overhead.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news|url=https://ultimatemotorcycling.com/2017/06/13/2017-yamaha-yzf-r3-review-12-fast-facts/|title=2017 Yamaha YZF-R3 Review {{!}} 12 Fast Facts|date=2017-06-13|work=Ultimate Motorcycling|access-date=2017-10-04|language=en-US}}</ref> The 321 cc performance-oriented engine is lightweight, powerful, and has a wide power band. Most of the power can be found from 7,000 rpm to [[redline]] (12,500 rpm approx.).<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> The engine uses a downdraft induction fuel injection system and the 10-spoke cast aluminum wheels reduce [[unsprung weight]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.yamahamotorsports.com/supersport/models/yzf-r3|title=2017 Yamaha YZF-R3 Supersport Motorcycle - Photo Gallery, Video, Specs, Features, Offers, Inventory and more|website=[[Yamaha]]|access-date=2017-09-13}}</ref> The cylinders are all-aluminum. For 2017, the YZF-R3 offers optional [[Anti-lock braking system|ABS]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> The 2018 Model has dual channel ABS and is EURO IV compliant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/2018-yamaha-r3-launched-at-rs-348-lakh-407296|title=2018 Yamaha R3 BS-IV launch, price, deliveries, details, specifications, engine, design and more - Autocar India|website=www.autocarindia.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== Performance, reviews and criticisms ==\nThe bike can reach {{Convert|0-60|km/h|abbr=on}} in less than 3 seconds, and {{Convert|0-100|km/h|abbr=on}} in 5.5 seconds.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bikedekho.com/yamaha/yzf-r3/road-test-yamaha-yzf-r3-road-test|title=Yamaha YZF R3: Expert Review {{!}} BikeDekho|website=www.bikedekho.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref> The 2015 R3 has a braking distance of 131.5 feet from {{Convert|100-0|km/h|abbr=on}}. According to some reviewers, the braking system is not powerful enough to match the engine power, and is also prone to fishtailing under hard braking (non ABS).<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zigwheels.com/reviews-advice/reviews/yamaha-r3-4000km-long-term-report/25273/|title=Yamaha YZF-R3: 4,000km Long Term Review|work=ZigWheels.com|access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref> However, [[engine braking]] can be used to assist deceleration, as the stock bike does not have a [[slipper clutch]].<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.zigwheels.com/news-features/news/yamaha-yzfr3-7-things-to-know/22755/|title=Yamaha YZF 3 -  7 things to know!}}</ref>  Minimal adjustable suspension is considered another downside on the bike.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bestbeginnermotorcycles.com/yamaha-r3-review/|title=Yamaha R3 Review- Pros, Cons, Specs & Ratings|date=2017-01-31|work=BestBeginnerMotorcycles|access-date=2017-10-04|language=en-US}}</ref> However, compared to other bikes in its class, it is considered finely tuned and sufficient.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\n== Rivals ==\nYamaha R3 competes directly with [[Kawasaki Ninja 300]]. Other entry level (250-400&nbsp;cc ) competitors include [[Honda CBR300R]], Suzuki GSXR-250 and [[KTM 390 series|KTM RC 390]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cycleworld.com/2015/05/18/four-affordable-sub-400cc-entry-level-sportbike-motorcycle-review-comparison-test-photos-specifications#page-4|title=Four Sub-400cc Entry-Level Sportbikes - COMPARISON TEST|work=Cycle World|access-date=2017-10-04|language=en}}</ref>{{clear}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://www.yamaha-motor.eu/eu/products/motorcycles/supersport/yzf-r3.aspx Official website (Europe)]\n\n{{Yamaha motorcycles}}\n\n[[Category:Yamaha motorcycles|YZF-R3]]\n[[Category:Sport bikes]]\n[[Category:Motorcycles introduced in 2015]]\n[[Category:Motorcycles powered by straight-twin engines]]\n\n\n{{motorcycle-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Navinsingh133", "label": "safe", "comment": "Wikilink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yamaha_YZF-R3"}
